The following bundled file is licensed separately:

  tests/testthat/fixtures/forbes2023_amh.rds

    Contains the 155-variable "Assessing Mental Health" (AMH) Spearman
    correlation matrix from:

      Forbes, M. K. (2023). Improving hierarchical models of individual
      differences: An extension of Goldberg's bass-ackward method.
      Psychological Methods. https://doi.org/10.1037/met0000546

    Source: OSF project https://osf.io/pcwm8/ (file corSpearman_AMH.csv,
    guid s9bjz). The matrix is redistributed here under its original license,

      Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International (CC-BY 4.0)
      https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/

    with attribution to M. K. Forbes as above. The accompanying expected
    between-level correlations and loading congruences stored in the same
    file were computed from that matrix using Forbes's own reference
    implementation ("ExtendedBassAckwards functions with annotation.R",
    guid 7jfkw, same OSF project and license). The file is used only by the
    package's test suite. See data-raw/forbes2023_amh.R for provenance.
